			=09
				<div class=3D"listing listingCollapse single">		<dl>
		<dt>
How many gallons of water are in an acre-foot?		</dt>
		<dd class=3D"fr-view">
There are 325,850 gallons in 1 acre-foot.		</dd>
	</dl>
</div>
<div class=3D"listing listingCollapse">
	<div id=3D"cat16">
		<a class=3D"translatable active" tabindex=3D"0" role=3D"button" data-cp-t=
oggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"16" aria-expanded=3D"true" title=3D"Cli=
ck to expand/collapse this category">
			<h2>
Canal Water Service		</h2>
		</a>
	</div>
	<div id=3D"16">
	<div>
	  <p class=3D"showHide"><a id=3D"p_16" role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"c=
ollapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_69 dd_70 dd_71 dd_72 dd_73 dd_74 dd_75 dd_76 d=
d_77 dd_78 dd_79 dd_80 dd_81 dd_82 dd_83 dd_84 dd_85 dd_86 dd_87 dd_88 dd_8=
9 dd_90" aria-expanded=3D"false" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#" data-cp-toggle-inactive-title=3D"Show All Answers" data-cp-toggle-active=
-title=3D"Hide All Answers">Show All Answers</a></p>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">1.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_69" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_69" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">Why am I unable to order a 12-hour for today? </a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_6=
9">
If you need to place a same day order there will be an extra charge involve=
d (the order will be considered an =E2=80=9Cunscheduled on=E2=80=9D) and we=
 cannot guarantee a 12-hour order for that same day. We have delivery restr=
aints due to lateral flow capabilities. If you are ordering water for the n=
ext day then you can place the order online. Orders for the next day should=
 be placed by 11 a.m. the day prior so that we may accurately manage water =
needs for all users.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">2.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_70" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_70" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">How many gallons of water are in an acre-foot?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_7=
0">
There are 325,850 gallons in 1 acre-foot.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">3.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_71" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_71" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">Are there conversion formulas to assist with CFS (cubic feet per second)=
 water calculations?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_7=
1">
One cubic-foot per second (or 7.48 gallons per second) is also equal to 448=
.8 gallons per minute, 1 CFS =3D miner's feet. Please see the table for add=
itional conversions.			<a href=3D"https://cvwd.org/197">Conversion Table</a=
>
			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">4.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_72" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_72" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">How do I read my meter?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_7=
2">
There are different types of meters we use in our distribution system; howe=
ver they all serve the same purpose. Some are digital and others are the mo=
re traditional clock-like meters. The function remains the same. The order =
is measured by the movement of water flowing through a boat-like propeller =
within the meter tube, and based on how rapidly it spins; it is how the vol=
ume of water flowing through the meter is determined. Questions regarding y=
our particular meter can be addressed at your initial introductory meeting.=
 For existing customers, please call our irrigation line at 760-398-2611 fo=
r assistance.			<a href=3D"https://cvwd.org/DocumentCenter/View/874" target=
=3D"_blank" aria-label=3D"Examples of Water Meters (JPG) Opens in new windo=
w" rel=3D"noopener">Examples of Water Meters (JPG)</a>
			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">5.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_73" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_73" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">What types of services charges will I incur?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_7=
3">
Please see our water rates page for detailed information.			<a href=3D"http=
s://cvwd.org/198">Water Rates</a>
			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">6.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_74" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_74" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">How do I know how much water to order if it=E2=80=99s my first time?</a>=
</dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_7=
4">
For the first order, we will assist you to effectively determine watering p=
atterns for future orders. Once you apply and are approved for a canal wate=
r account we will send a representative out to meet with you at your meter.=
 This process may take as long as 3 to 4 weeks to complete.<p><br>The proce=
ss involves setting up your account, testing your meter and delivery valves=
 to determine any further work that must be done on our part prior to deliv=
ering your first order. We will make sure that all valves and your meter ar=
e working properly. We will review specifics regarding how your meter measu=
res water. We will go over what type of crop you will be watering and work =
with you to determine the most accurate amount of water necessary.			</p></=
dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">7.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_75" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_75" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">I was told that a zanjero will be coming out to my meter? What or who is=
 a zanjero?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_7=
5">
The definition varies depending on what source you use. A zanjero is an ind=
ividual that manages the irrigation distribution system. Some of his tasks =
include turning valves, reading meters, and monitoring flows to insure deli=
very to the customer.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">8.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_76" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_76" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">How long does it take to receive my water once the zanjero opens the met=
er?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_7=
6">
There are 2 main factors that determine the answer. It depends on how many =
other users have ordered water for the same day, and the specific location =
on the delivery line that your meter occupies. It could take a matter of mi=
nutes or up to several hours. If you are a new user, this will be one of th=
e topics we discuss with you when we meet with you at your meter as part of=
 our introductory session.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">9.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_77" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_77" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">I was told that my meter has been prorated for today=E2=80=99s order. Wh=
at does that mean?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_7=
7">
At certain times the amount of water ordered will exceed the capacity of th=
e lateral (underground piping) serving your meter. When this happens the us=
ers with orders will each have their order cut back proportionately to even=
ly distribute the amount of water available to that specific lateral. The z=
anjero will then notify our Customer Service Representatives with the speci=
fic prorated amounts for each user.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">10.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_78" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_78" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">How much water can I order if I use a pump?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_7=
8">
Our system is gravity based. The use of a pump enhances this system. Howeve=
r, even with the use of a pump the amount of water ordered still will depen=
d upon the lateral=E2=80=99s capacity. A normal meter capacity will be 150"=
 (3 CFS). However our meters can vary, some have a capacity greater than or=
 less than 150".			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">11.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_79" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_79" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">What is a meant by a short, long, and intermediate delivery?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_7=
9">
<p>When there is more than 1 user on a meter, each has a designated deliver=
y point from which they irrigate. A <strong>short delivery</strong> is the =
closest acreage next to the meter. The district=E2=80=99s responsibility is=
 3 feet downstream of the short delivery valve. An <strong>intermediate del=
ivery</strong> is located off of the long delivery and is used to irrigate =
the next acreage downstream of the meter. The district=E2=80=99s responsibi=
lity is also only 3 feet downstream of the intermediate valve. A <strong>lo=
ng delivery</strong> is used to irrigate the furthest acreage to the south =
of the meter. The district=E2=80=99s responsibility is up to 1,300 feet fro=
m the long delivery valve. Any delivery lines or field valves past the poin=
ts mentioned above will be the user=E2=80=99s responsibility.</p>			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">12.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_80" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_80" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">What are the drawbacks of a 12-hour order vs. the benefits of 24-hour or=
der?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_8=
0">
A 12-hour order is basically an order that may be anywhere from 8-12 hours =
in length. The meter will get turned on between the hours of 6:30 and 11 a.=
m., and turned off toward the end of the day, between 5 and 9:30 p.m. A 12-=
hour run is problematic for the same reasons as an unscheduled order in tha=
t it will cause disruptions of service to the other users on the lateral. T=
he most common issue that will take place is a surge in the line. A 24-hour=
 order may be on anywhere from 22-24 hours in length. This type of order te=
nds to provide a more consistent flow. The variance in the length of the or=
der will depend upon how many meters are running on that particular day. Ty=
pically the laterals with 24-hour orders will have the least amount of deli=
very issues.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">13.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_81" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_81" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">I was told there is a surge in the line, what does that mean?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_8=
1">
A surge is caused by a change in the flow of water, pressure, air in the li=
ne, etc. the end result will be inconsistent deliveries to the meter. For e=
xample, in one instance you may receive 150" for a few seconds and then dro=
p down to 50" as this surge moves back and forth through the lateral line. =
A surge will work its way out of the line over a period of hours however th=
e adjustments to the lateral will cause the surge to continue for a longer =
period of time.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">14.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_82" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_82" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">Will I be informed whenever the distribution system requires maintenance=
?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_8=
2">
Yes, our website has a daily list of irrigation repairs that will be taking=
 place. For planned repairs that involve an entire lateral a letter will be=
 sent out to customers in advance. For repairs that involve only a few cust=
omers, phone calls will be made. If an emergency outage occurs and an immed=
iate shut down is required, we will contact our Customer Service Representa=
tives so that if you do call in to inquire about water outages they will be=
 able to inform you of the disruption in service and any other pertinent in=
formation that might be available.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">15.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_83" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_83" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">If my meter doesn=E2=80=99t register, do I still get charged for using w=
ater?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_8=
3">
Yes, at times your meter register may become broken; when this occurs our z=
anjeros are able to determine the amount of flow by the number of valve tur=
n openings they execute. All meters that have active orders are assessed ev=
ery day to make sure that the delivery is constant. When a meter is found t=
o be broken a work order is immediately executed and the meter is scheduled=
 for repairs.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">16.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_84" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_84" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">Can you give me a brief history of the canal distribution system and how=
 it functions?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_8=
4">
The Coachella Canal is a 123 mile (196 km) aqueduct that conveys Colorado R=
iver water for irrigation from the All-American Canal to the Coachella Vall=
ey in Riverside County, California. Construction of the Coachella Canal beg=
an in the 1930=E2=80=99s by Six Companies, Inc., but was interrupted by Wor=
ld War II. After the war, work was resumed on the canal. The canal was comp=
leted in 1949 and water deliveries began at that time. The canal is current=
ly operated by the Coachella Valley Water District.<p><br>The canal distrib=
ution system was constructed and engineered to follow the natural slope of =
the land to allow the free flow of water in the direction of the force of g=
ravity. Irrigation pumps are used to deliver water to elevated areas within=
 the availability zones.			</p></dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">17.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_85" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_85" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">Why am I not allowed to =E2=80=9Cwork=E2=80=9D my own meter?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_8=
5">
There are many factors to consider in this answer: District liabilities (le=
galities and safe practices), prevention of damages that can occur (both di=
strict and private), disruption of service to other customers, and protecti=
on of users from liabilities for mishandling district property.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">18.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_86" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_86" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">What is a split order?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_8=
6">
A split order occurs when 2 or more users have orders for the same time per=
iod, on the same meter. Water will then be divided between / amongst the us=
ers. If a problem arises with 1 of the users (either the amount of water th=
ey are receiving or the amount of water ordered exceeds the capacity of the=
 meter), then the user who placed their order first gets priority for the d=
uration of his or her order. All subsequent users will be turned off. If th=
e users are able to work together and modify their original requests, the d=
istrict will do its best to provide all users with water (by prorating all =
deliveries).			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">19.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_87" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_87" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">What is an emergency off?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_8=
7">
<p>An emergency off is when a user calls in and needs their water turned of=
f immediately. Once the district is notified that an emergency off has been=
 requested, a zanjero will promptly make his way to the meter and turn it o=
ff.</p>			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">20.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_88" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_88" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">Is there such thing as an "emergency on"?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_8=
8">
Yes, but only when the "emergency on" is requested by the Fire Department t=
o battle a fire in an area that is adjacent to one of our irrigation meters=
.			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">21.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_89" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_89" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">If I request a non-emergency off or an unscheduled on, how long do I hav=
e to wait for the task to be completed?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_8=
9">
The time period will vary. The zanjero has to follow a specific route to fu=
lfill his scheduled orders. If the zanjero has passed the specific meter, h=
e must complete his route and then return to the meter that has requested t=
he unscheduled "on or off."			</dd>
		</dl>
		<dl>
			<dt>
				<span class=3D"questionCount">22.</span>
<a role=3D"button" data-cp-toggle=3D"collapse" aria-controls=3D"dd_90" aria=
-expanded=3D"false" id=3D"dt_90" href=3D"https://cvwd.org/FAQ.aspx?QID=3D70=
#">How much water am I allowed to order?</a></dt>
			<dd class=3D"fr-view" style=3D"display:none;" name=3D"dd__16" id=3D"dd_9=
0">
A user can order up to the capacity of their delivery system or the capacit=
y of the district=E2=80=99s lateral and meter. A customer may request to me=
et district personnel for testing to be performed to determine the maximum =
amount of water they can order. The amount delivered to a specific meter ma=
y vary day to day depending on the total number of orders on the line that =
serves that meter.			</dd>
		</dl>
		</div>
	</div>
	</div>

